data.text:
Dodge County

Dodge county is located in south Minnesota. Dodge county has 439.28 square miles of land area and 0.31 square miles of water area. As of 2010-2014, the total Dodge county population is 20,246, which has grown 14.18% since 2000. The population growth rate is higher than the state average rate of 9.44% and is higher than the national average rate of 11.61%. Dodge county median household income is $68,587 in 2010-2014 and has grown by 44.59% since 2000. The income growth rate is much higher than the state average rate of 29.12% and is much higher than the national average rate of 27.36%. Dodge county median house value is $160,200 in 2010-2014 and has grown by 64.98% since 2000. The house value growth rate is higher than the state average rate of 51.31% and is higher than the national average rate of 46.91%. As a reference, the national Consumer Price Index (CPI) inflation rate for the same period is 26.63%. On average, the public school district that covers Dodge county is better than the state average in quality. The Dodge county area code is 507.
